  "name": "trust_topology_audit_curvenet",
  "source": "trust_topology_audit",
  "description": "Apply the trust_topology_audit domain to the V-Sekai-fire/TOOL_godot_curvenet project. Identifies the existing gates (Lean native_decide proofs across 23 modules; RapidCheck property tests across 13 binaries; lake build; scons -j8 build; manual editor verification on Mire), then walks the four diagnostic properties: overlap ratio (Lean vs RC redundancy), verification amplification (Lean → C++ → tests → editor chain), deterministic ceiling (provable proofs vs manual UX judgement vs unobservable artist intent), and the liveness constraint (current gate budget vs throughput). Synthesises recommendations such as adding a real-rig deformation-quality gate that runs the full deformer on Mire and an explicit oracle-routing path for hard-failure escalation. Final artifact is a docs/AUDIT_TRUST_TOPOLOGY.md narrative committed to the project tree.",
